  "text": "Both, the random distribution of insertion sites and the low rate of large deletions affecting more than one gene are benefits of our method. Contrary to our experience with MAH, Collins and colleagues [CITATION_1] observed more clustered insertions and deletions of up to 12 genes by mutagenising M. bovis with a DNA fragment carrying a Kanamycin resistance gene by illegitimate recombination. It would be interesting to find out the reasons for these differing outcomes. Are the specific parameters of the illegitimate recombination events species-specific or does the composition of the recombination substrate play a more important role?",
